Port Elizabeth - A mother of four was arrested after she allegedly left her four children alone while she visited her boyfriend, Eastern Cape police said on Tuesday. Police spokesperson, Captain Nkosikho Mzuku said the 29-year-old mother allegedly left her children with no food to eat at the weekend in Mdantsane. The children are aged four, six, eight and nine. Mzuku said the older siblings also could not attend school as they were babysitting the four-year-old. Members of the community intervened and reported the matter to social workers. The woman was arrested on Monday and a case of child neglect was opened at the Mdantsane Police Station. She is expected to appear in the Mdantsane Magistrateâ€™s Court this week. African News Agency/ANA